            <subdebate.1>
                <subdebateinfo>
                    <title>COMMONWEALTH MAKINE SUPERINTENDENT</title>
                    <page.no>8608</page.no>
                </subdebateinfo>
                <question>
                    <talk.start>
                        <talker>
                            <page.no>8608</page.no>
                            <time.stamp />
                            <name.id>KNB</name.id>
                            <electorate></electorate>
                            <party />
                            <role></role>
                            <in.gov>0</in.gov>
                            <first.speech>0</first.speech>
                            <name role="metadata">GUTHRIE, Robert</name>
                            <name role="display">Senator GUTHRIE</name>
                        </talker>
                        <para>- Will the Assistant Minister say whether it is a fact, as announced in this morning's newspapers, that a Marine Superintendent has been appointed for the Commonwealth fleet of steam-ships? </para>
                    </talk.start>
                </question>
                <answer>
                    <talk.start>
                        <talker>
                            <page.no>8608</page.no>
                            <time.stamp />
                            <name.id>K3E</name.id>
                            <electorate></electorate>
                            <party>ALP</party>
                            <role></role>
                            <in.gov>1</in.gov>
                            <first.speech>0</first.speech>
                            <name role="metadata">RUSSELL, Edward</name>
                            <name role="display">Senator RUSSELL</name>
                        </talker>
                        <para>- Yes; the announcement is perfectly correct. </para>
                    </talk.start>
                    <continue>
                        <talk.start>
                            <talker>
                                <page.no>8608</page.no>
                                <time.stamp />
                                <name.id>KNB</name.id>
                                <electorate />
                                <party />
                                <role />
                                <in.gov>0</in.gov>
                                <first.speech>0</first.speech>
                                <name role="metadata">GUTHRIE, Robert</name>
                                <name role="display">Senator GUTHRIE</name>
                            </talker>
                            <para>- Arising out of the answer to the question, I should like to ask whether applications were called for the position, and if not, why not? </para>
                        </talk.start>
                    </continue>
                    <continue>
                        <talk.start>
                            <talker>
                                <page.no>8608</page.no>
                                <time.stamp />
                                <name.id>K3E</name.id>
                                <electorate />
                                <party />
                                <role />
                                <in.gov>0</in.gov>
                                <first.speech>0</first.speech>
                                <name role="metadata">RUSSELL, Edward</name>
                                <name role="display">Senator RUSSELL</name>
                            </talker>
                            <para>- The appointment is quite a temporary one, for on month only. </para>
                        </talk.start>
                    </continue>
                </answer>
            </subdebate.1>
            <subdebate.1>
                <subdebateinfo>
                    <title>FEDERAL CAPITAL</title>
                    <page.no>8608</page.no>
                </subdebateinfo>
                <para>Engagement of Mr.c. E. Oliver. </para>
                <question>
                    <talk.start>
                        <talker>
                            <page.no>8608</page.no>
                            <time.stamp />
                            <name.id>K7L</name.id>
                            <electorate></electorate>
                            <party />
                            <role></role>
                            <in.gov>0</in.gov>
                            <first.speech>0</first.speech>
                            <name role="metadata">STORY, William</name>
                            <name role="display">Senator STORY</name>
                        </talker>
                        <para>- Will the Minister representing the Minister for Home Affairs cause to he laid on the table of the Senate all papers relating to the employment of <inline font-weight="bold">Mr. C.</inline> E. Oliver to report on the sanitary systems of the Federal Capital? </para>
                    </talk.start>
                </question>
                <answer>
                        <talk.start>
                            <talker>
                                <page.no>8608</page.no>
                                <time.stamp />
                                <name.id>K3E</name.id>
                                <electorate />
                                <party>ALP</party>
                                <role />
                                <in.gov>1</in.gov>
                                <first.speech>0</first.speech>
                                <name role="metadata">RUSSELL, Edward</name>
                                <name role="display">Senator RUSSELL</name>
                            </talker>
                            <para>- I understand that if the papers were laid on the table of the Senate they would become the property of the Senate. I can undertake to have them laid on the table of the Library. </para>
                        </talk.start>
                </answer>
            </subdebate.1>
            <subdebate.1>
                <subdebateinfo>
                    <title>CONSCRIPTION REFERENDUM</title>
                    <page.no>8608</page.no>
                </subdebateinfo>
                <question>
                    <talk.start>
                        <talker>
                            <page.no>8608</page.no>
                            <time.stamp />
                            <name.id>KMP</name.id>
                            <electorate></electorate>
                            <party />
                            <role></role>
                            <in.gov>0</in.gov>
                            <first.speech>0</first.speech>
                            <name role="metadata">GRANT, John</name>
                            <name role="display">Senator GRANT</name>
                        </talker>
                        <para>- In view of the widespread belief that those who are opposed to conscription will not, during the referendum campaign, be given a fair opportunity to express their views, because of the instructions given to the censors, I should like the Minister for Defence to say whether opponents of conscription may rest assured that the fullest possible opportunity will be given them to carry on their campaign in the event of the passing of the Military Service Referendum Bill? </para>
                    </talk.start>
                </question>
                <answer>
                    <talk.start>
                        <talker>
                            <page.no>8608</page.no>
                            <time.stamp />
                            <name.id>K0F</name.id>
                            <electorate></electorate>
                            <party>ALP</party>
                            <role></role>
                            <in.gov>1</in.gov>
                            <first.speech>0</first.speech>
                            <name role="metadata">PEARCE, George</name>
                            <name role="display">Senator PEARCE</name>
                        </talker>
                        <para>- Subject to certain rules which have been laid down, yes. </para>
                    </talk.start>
                </answer>
            </subdebate.1>
        </debate>
