        <debate>
            <debateinfo>
                <title>SPECIAL ADJOURNMENT</title>
                <page.no>8608</page.no>
                <type>special adjournment</type>
            </debateinfo>
            <speech>
                <talk.start>
                    <talker>
                        <page.no>8608</page.no>
                        <time.stamp />
                        <name.id>K0F</name.id>
                        <electorate>Western Australia</electorate>
                        <party>ALP</party>
                        <role>Minister for Defence</role>
                        <in.gov>1</in.gov>
                        <first.speech>0</first.speech>
                        <name role="metadata">PEARCE, George</name>
                        <name role="display">Senator PEARCE</name>
                    </talker>
                    <para>. - I move - </para>
                </talk.start>
                <quote>
                    <para>That the Senate, at its rising, adjourn till 3 p.m. on Thursday next. </para>
                </quote>
                <para class="block">I understand that it is expected that the Military Service Referendum Bill will pass in another place on Wednesday next, and I ask honorable senators to come on </para>
                <para class="block">Thursday prepared to go right on with that Bill. They are aware of its purport and contents, and I hope I shall get the consent. of the Senate to the adoption of that course. </para>
                <interjection>
                    <talk.start>
                        <talker>
                            <page.no>8609</page.no>
                            <time.stamp />
                            <name.id>JYX</name.id>
                            <electorate />
                            <party />
                            <role />
                            <in.gov>0</in.gov>
                            <first.speech>0</first.speech>
                            <name role="metadata">FINDLEY, Edward</name>
                            <name role="display">Senator Findley</name>
                        </talker>
                        <para>-  What does the honorable senator mean by going right on with the Bill? </para>
                    </talk.start>
                </interjection>
                <continue>
                    <talk.start>
                        <talker>
                            <page.no>8609</page.no>
                            <time.stamp />
                            <name.id>K0F</name.id>
                            <electorate />
                            <party />
                            <role />
                            <in.gov>0</in.gov>
                            <first.speech>0</first.speech>
                            <name role="metadata">PEARCE, George</name>
                            <name role="display">Senator PEARCE</name>
                        </talker>
                        <para>- I meat that we should take the first and second readings stages on Thursday; in other words, that on that day we should go on with the second-reading debate. </para>
                    </talk.start>
                </continue>
                <interjection>
                    <talk.start>
                        <talker>
                            <page.no>8609</page.no>
                            <time.stamp />
                            <name.id>K5V</name.id>
                            <electorate />
                            <party />
                            <role />
                            <in.gov>0</in.gov>
                            <first.speech>0</first.speech>
                            <name role="metadata">SHANNON, John</name>
                            <name role="display">Senator Shannon</name>
                        </talker>
                        <para>-  Which will result in a late sitting. </para>
                    </talk.start>
                </interjection>
                <continue>
                    <talk.start>
                        <talker>
                            <page.no>8609</page.no>
                            <time.stamp />
                            <name.id>K0F</name.id>
                            <electorate />
                            <party />
                            <role />
                            <in.gov>0</in.gov>
                            <first.speech>0</first.speech>
                            <name role="metadata">PEARCE, George</name>
                            <name role="display">Senator PEARCE</name>
                        </talker>
                        <para>- I hope that it will not be necessary to have a late sitting. Following the ordinary course it would be possible only to take the formal stage of the first reading of the Bill on Thursday, and I am therefore asking honorable senators to come prepared to go on with the second-reading debate on that day. If necessary, it may be extended to the following day. In view of the large amount of machinery to be provided in connexion with the Bill, and in view of the fact that we must have the authority of the Bill to put some of that machinery into operation, it is the desire of the Government to have the Bill passed next week, if possible. </para>
                    </talk.start>
                </continue>
                <para>Question resolved in the affirmative. </para>
            </speech>
        </debate>
